Unabomber suspect theodore j. kaczynski pleaded innocent today via video to charges he sent the mail bomb killing an advertising executive exactly two years ago.
Kaczynski's plea from california was made through a live hookup to the federal courthouse in newark where judge dickinson r. debevoise presided in a courtroom, the associated press reported.
Kaczynski 54-year- is accused of being the unabomber, who killed three people and injured 23 during a campaign against technology between 1978 and 1995.
